[2026-05-03T08:05:00Z] Branch feat/auth-defects-fix off main
  Two production auth defects assigned:
    1. Signup confirmation email not delivering reliably.
    2. /auth/reset-password hang on "Updating password".
  Session 3 (admin/marketing) flagged auth files as out-of-scope per
  CLAUDE.md domain split; this session owns the fix.

[2026-05-03T08:10:00Z] Defect 2 fix landed (commit da27eb9)
  Root cause: success path called signOut() then router.push() with no
  finally to reset loading. signOut() can deadlock on NavigatorLock and
  the global unhandledrejection handler swallows the surfaced error.
  Fix: try/finally always resets loading; updateUser raced against 15s
  timeout; signOut demoted to 3s best-effort cleanup; hard navigation
  via window.location.assign so SPA router does not intercept.

[2026-05-03T08:30:00Z] Defect 1 fix landed (commit d861c19)
  Root cause: client supabase.auth.signUp drove confirmation email via
  Supabase Auth's default outbound SMTP (4 emails/hr project-wide cap).
  Once signup volume crossed that floor, mail was silently dropped
  with no error surface anywhere.
  Fix: server-side endpoint /api/auth/signup that creates the user via
  admin.auth.admin.generateLink({type:'signup'}) and dispatches the
  branded confirmation directly via the Resend SDK. Bypasses Supabase
  SMTP entirely. Adds auth-signup rate-limit policy (5 per IP per 10
  min). Rolls back the user record on send failure to avoid stranded
  half-created accounts. EMAIL_FROM env var documented in .env.example.

